A new PR for a new patch is up. This addresses a resurfaced exploit. Credit goes to @HippoHoppy and @Noah for helping uncover the root cause

1. a while back we introduced a patch that subtracted the amount from `Burn` events for positions.  We did this because, when an LP manually `burn()`s a position the liquidity gets accounted as uncollected fees, and miners were gaming this by depositing a ton of liquidity and instantly burning the position to make it look like they were making tens of thousands of dollars in fees.
2. 2 weeks ago we realized that when people decreased liquidity it would also be considered burn event, so if someone were to remove a sufficient amount of liquidity from their position it prevent them from receiving any emission.  So we implemented a patch to address try and address this.

What we didn't realize until recently is that with (2) we basically reverted the changes we made in (1), because now instead of miners manually `burn()`ing their positions they'd simply just remove all the liquidity from the position to rake up "uncollected fees".

We'll be merging this patch within the next hour 🫡 .
